    "updated_at": "2024-07-03T09:39:44Z",
    "body": "The whole config I'm working on [is here](https://github.com/alerque/que-zsh/blob/starship/.config/starship.toml). Note the current iteration there has a workaround my hard coding the colors in the right segment to avoid this bug.\r\n\r\nHere is what I expected to have work:\r\n\r\n```toml\r\nright_format = \"\"\"\r\n$status\r\n$cmd_duration\r\n$jobs\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\n[status]\r\ndisabled = false\r\nstyle = 'bg:dark_bg fg:alert'\r\nformat = '[](fg:dark_bg)[$symbol$common_meaning$signal_name ]($style)'\r\n\r\n[cmd_duration]\r\nstyle = \"bg:medium_bg fg:medium_fg\"\r\nformat = '[]($style bg:prev_bg fg:medium_bg)[ $duration ]($style)'\r\n\r\n[jobs]\r\nstyle = 'bold bg:light_bg fg:light_fg'\r\nformat = '[]($style bg:prev_bg fg:light_bg)[$symbol$number ]($style)'\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe values that don't work as expected here are the `bg:prev_bg` where the background of the separator character for the new segment is expected to match the background of the previous segment. As you can see in the workaround in my actual config I can e.g. make thet *jobs* separator background `bg:medium_bg` to hard code the previous segment, but that breaks when the *cmd_duration* segments decides not to display at all.",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
